sections.title: How the population has changed in East Riding of Yorkshire
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, East Riding of Yorkshire was the sixth largest local authority in Yorkshire and The Humber, with a total population of 343,201. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in Yorkshire and The Humber, 2002-2020
Population density in East Riding of Yorkshire
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in East Riding of Yorkshire was 143 people per square kilometre, which was less than Yorkshire and The Humber (359), and less than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in Yorkshire and The Humber, 2020
Median age in East Riding of Yorkshire
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in East Riding of Yorkshire was 50 years, which was older than Yorkshire and The Humber (40 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
